Context:
The Entry Advising team at George Brown College provides assistance with questions and concerns regarding college entry. They offer group sessions for common requests and individual appointments of up to 30 minutes for topics not covered in the group sessions. Interested individuals can sign up to receive updates on application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, tours, and more by submitting an appointment request form. The contact information for Entry Advising is a phone number (416-415-2000) and a TTY number (1-877-515-5559), as well as an email address (ask.george@georgebrown.ca). The college's land acknowledgment can also be learned more about on the website.

The provided information is subject to change without notice and should not be considered a representation, offer, or warranty. Students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements. The text does not explicitly state any program names offered by the college. Therefore, there is no key information related to specific programs in this text.
